name: Celebi & Venusaur-GX
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned, Confused, and Poisoned.

name: Weedle
flavorText: Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.

name: Weedle
flavorText: Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Kakuna
flavorText: Almost incapable of moving, this Pokémon can only harden its shell to protect itself when it is in danger.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has any Grass Energy attached to it, it takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Beedrill
flavorText: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.
Attack1Text: You can use this attack only if this Pokémon has any damage counters on it. Both Active Pokémon are Knocked Out.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Paras
flavorText: Whether it's due to a lack of moisture or a lack of nutrients, in Alola the mushrooms on Paras don't grow up quite right.

name: Parasect
flavorText: The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.
Ability1Text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Confused Pokémon between turns.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Exeggcute
flavorText: Six of them form a single Pokémon. Should one of the six be lost, the next morning there will once more be six.
Attack1Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Pinsir
flavorText: It gets into territorial disputes with Vikavolt. For some reason, it apparently gets along well with Heracross in Alola.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is Knocked Out.

name: Shaymin ◇
flavorText: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage times the amount of basic Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.

name: Charmander
flavorText: The flame on its tail indicates Charmander's life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Charmander
flavorText: The flame on its tail indicates Charmander's life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: It lashes about with its tail to knock down its foe. It then tears up the fallen opponent with sharp claws.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Charizard
flavorText: When expelling a blast of superhot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns more intensely.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put 2 damage counters on this Pokémon. If you do, search your deck for up to 2 Fire Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Discard all Fire Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 50 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Vulpix
flavorText: Its beautiful tails have made it very popular. However, if it's not brushed diligently, it will be a mass of tangles before you know it.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Ninetales
flavorText: It is vindictive and relentless by nature. Those who cross it even once will be cursed for a thousand years, along with their descendants.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard 2 Fire Energy cards from your hand. If you do, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.

name: Ponyta
flavorText: As a newborn, it can barely stand. However, through galloping, its legs are made tougher and faster.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Rapidash
flavorText: Very competitive, this Pokémon will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

name: Moltres
flavorText: It is said to be the legendary bird Pokémon of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flare of flames.
Attack1Text: Discard all Fire Energy from this Pokémon. Then, discard a card from the top of your opponent's deck for each Energy you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: Discard 3 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Litten
flavorText: It doesn't allow its emotions to be easily seen. Earning its trust takes time. It prefers solitude.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Torracat
flavorText: It boasts powerful front legs. With a single punch, it can bend an iron bar right over.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

name: Squirtle
flavorText: It shelters itself in its shell, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.
Ability1Text: If you have a Stadium card in play, this Pokémon has no Retreat Cost.

name: Squirtle
flavorText: It shelters itself in its shell, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.

name: Wartortle
flavorText: When tapped, this Pokémon will pull in its head, but its tail will still stick out a little bit.

name: Blastoise
flavorText: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may look at the top 6 cards of your deck and attach any number of Water Energy cards you find there to your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon does 30 damage to itself.

name: Psyduck
flavorText: Using psychokinesis gives it a headache, so it normally passes the time spacing out and doing as little as possible.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent can't play any Trainer cards from their hand during their next turn.

name: Golduck
flavorText: Even fast-swimming fish Pokémon can be disabled by Golduck. It brings them to a standstill and seizes them.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks. That Pokémon can't use that attack during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: If any of your opponent's Pokémon have any Water Energy attached to them, you may do 90 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon instead of their Active Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Staryu
flavorText: In many places, there are folktales of stardust falling into the ocean and becoming Staryu.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Magikarp
flavorText: In the distant past, they were fairly strong, but they have become gradually weaker over time.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, put a card that evolves from this Pokémon from your discard pile onto this Pokémon to evolve it.

name: Gyarados
flavorText: It fires hyper beams in all directions, burning the surrounding area to ash. There are some regions where it's called "the deity of destruction."
Attack1Text: Reveal the top 7 cards of your deck. This attack does 30 more damage times the amount of Water Energy you find there. Then, shuffle those Energy cards back into your deck and discard the other cards.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Lapras
flavorText: It likes swimming around with people on its back. In the Alola region, it's an important means of transportation over water.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage times the amount of Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Articuno
flavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, whenever your opponent plays a Supporter card from their hand, prevent all effects of that card done to your Benched Water Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Move 2 Water Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Pikachu & Zekrom-GX
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Lightning Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has at least 3 extra Lightning Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), this attack does 170 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Alolan Geodude
flavorText: If you mistake it for a rock and step on it, it will headbutt you in anger. In addition to the pain, it will also zap you with a shock.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon does 60 damage to itself.

name: Alolan Geodude
flavorText: If you mistake it for a rock and step on it, it will headbutt you in anger. In addition to the pain, it will also zap you with a shock.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Lightning Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Alolan Graveler
flavorText: When two Graveler fight each other, it fills the surroundings with flashes of light and sound. People call it the "fireworks of the earth."

name: Alolan Golem
flavorText: It's grumpy and stubborn. If you upset it, it discharges electricity from the surface of its body and growls with a voice like thunder.
Attack1Text: Move any number of Lightning Energy from your Benched Pokémon to this Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage for each Energy card you moved in this way.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Voltorb
flavorText: It was discovered when Poké Balls were introduced. It is said that there is some connection.

name: Electrode
flavorText: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of "The Bomb Ball."
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may move any number of Lightning Energy from your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Zapdos
flavorText: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon was on the Bench and became your Active Pokémon this turn, this attack does 70 more damage. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness.

name: Mareep
flavorText: It stores lots of air in its soft fur, allowing it to stay cool in summer and warm in winter.
Attack1Text: Discard all Lightning Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Flaaffy
flavorText: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.
Attack2Text: Discard all Lightning Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Ampharos-GX
Attack1Text: Put all Electropower cards from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: Discard all Lightning Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Blitzle
flavorText: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Electropower cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Zebstrika
flavorText: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon evolved from Blitzle during this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Emolga
flavorText: It grills berries and bug Pokémon with electric shocks and makes a meal of them. It usually nests in the holes gouged in trees by Pikipek.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Pokémon that has the Nuzzle attack, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Joltik
flavorText: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Galvantula
flavorText: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.
Ability1Text: Whenever your opponent plays an Item or Supporter card from their hand, prevent all effects of that card done to this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Put a card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Helioptile
flavorText: The frills on either side of its head have cells that generate electricity when exposed to sunlight.

name: Heliolisk
flavorText: It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Lightning Pokémon.

name: Tapu Koko ◇
flavorText: It confuses its enemies by flying too quickly for the eye to follow. It has a hair-trigger temper but forgets what made it angry an instant later.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may choose 2 of your Benched Pokémon and attach a Lightning Energy card from your discard pile to each of them. If you do, discard all cards from this Pokémon and put it in the Lost Zone.

name: Zeraora
flavorText: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they'll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

name: Gengar & Mimikyu-GX
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. This attack does 50 damage for each Trainer card you find there.
Attack2Text: Your opponent can't play any cards from their hand during their next turn. If this Pokémon has at least 1 extra Psychic Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), each player draws cards until they have 7 cards in their hand. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Nidoran ♀
flavorText: Although small, its venomous barbs render this Pokémon dangerous. The female has smaller horns.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Nidorina
flavorText: The female has a gentle temperament. It emits ultrasonic cries that have the power to befuddle foes.
Attack1Text: Shuffle 5 Psychic Pokémon from your discard pile into your deck.

name: Nidoqueen
flavorText: It uses its scaly, rugged body to seal the entrance of its nest and protect its young from predators.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Pokémon that isn't a Pokémon-GX or Pokémon-EX, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Evolution Pokémon on your Bench.

name: Nidoran ♂
flavorText: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.

name: Nidorino
flavorText: It raises its big ears to check its surroundings. If it senses anything, it attacks immediately.

name: Nidoking
flavorText: It is recognized by its rock-hard hide and its extended horn. Be careful with the horn, as it contains venom.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon. This attack does 50 damage to the new Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If Nidoqueen is on your Bench, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Tentacool
flavorText: It drifts through the sea searching for prey. Its poisonous tentacles break off sometimes, but after a while, they grow back.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Tentacruel
flavorText: It fires off ultrasonic waves from its red orbs to weaken its prey, and then it wraps them up in its 80 tentacles.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Ultra Beasts.

name: Grimer
flavorText: It was born from sludge on the ocean floor. In a sterile environment, the germs within its body can't multiply, and it dies.

name: Muk
flavorText: Their food sources have decreased, and their numbers have declined sharply. Sludge ponds are being built to prevent their extinction.
Ability1Text: The Special Condition Poisoned is not removed when your opponent's Pokémon evolve or devolve.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. Put 2 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokémon between turns.

name: Alolan Marowak
flavorText: Its custom is to mourn its lost companions. Mounds of dirt by the side of the road mark the graves of the Marowak.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Pokémon in play that has Alolan in its name.

name: Starmie
flavorText: Its sparkling core is called "the gem of the sea." This core can be made into high-priced accessories that are traded in secret.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 in any combination of Water and Psychic Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Mr. Mime
flavorText: Its pantomime skills are wonderful. You may become enraptured while watching it, but next thing you know, Mr. Mime has made a real wall.
Ability1Text: Your opponent's Pokémon that have any damage counters on them, and any cards attached to those Pokémon, can't be put into your opponent's hand.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Mr. Mime-GX
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by your opponent's attacks if that damage is exactly 10, 30, 50, 70, 90, 110, 130, 150, 170, 190, 210, 230, or 250.
Attack1Text: For each card in your opponent's hand, put 1 damage counter on their Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Heal all damage from this Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Jynx
flavorText: It sways its hips to a rhythm all its own. The precise movements of Jynx living in Alola are truly wonderful.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: For each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon, put 1 damage counter on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Cosmog
flavorText: In ages past, it was called the child of the stars. It's said to be a Pokémon from another world, but no specific details are known.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Cosmoem
flavorText: There's something accumulating around the black core within its hard shell. People think this Pokémon may come from another world.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Mankey
flavorText: The smallest of things could cause it to lose its temper. Because it doesn't hold in its stress, this Pokémon can live a long time.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand.

name: Primeape
flavorText: It will never forgive opponents who have angered it. Even after it has beaten them down until they can't move, it never ever forgives.
Attack2Text: If there is any Stadium card in play, this attack does 80 more damage. Then, discard that Stadium card.

name: Hitmonlee
flavorText: The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.
Attack1Text: You can use this attack only if your Hitmonchan used Hit and Run during your last turn. This attack does 90 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Hitmonchan
flavorText: The arm-twisting punches it throws pulverize even concrete. It rests after three minutes of fighting.
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Omanyte
flavorText: Omanyte lived in the seas of antiquity. Its fossils have been found bearing bite marks from Archeops, so apparently Archeops preyed on it.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Omastar
flavorText: Its heavy shell is thought to be the reason this ancient Pokémon died out. It's apparently a distant ancestor of Octillery.
Ability1Text: As long as you have fewer Pokémon in play than your opponent, they can't play any Item cards from their hand.

name: Kabuto
flavorText: This Pokémon thrived 300 million years ago. It's said that living specimens can still be seen in a certain region—a rare sight.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Kabutops
flavorText: Its body had begun to change so it could function on land. But it didn't adapt in time and went extinct.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent can't play any Supporter cards from their hand.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Larvitar
flavorText: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Pupitar
flavorText: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has exactly 1 Prize card remaining, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Pancham
flavorText: There's no point to the leaf in its mouth, aside from an effort to look cool. It's mischievous, so it's not well suited to inexperienced Trainers.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Lycanroc-GX
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage for each Energy card in your opponent's discard pile. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Alolan Grimer
flavorText: The crystals on Grimer's body are lumps of toxins. If one falls off, lethal poisons leak out.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Special Condition affecting your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Alolan Muk
flavorText: While it's unexpectedly quiet and friendly, if it's not fed any trash for a while, it will smash its Trainer's furnishings and eat up the fragments.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may look at the top 6 cards of your opponent's deck and discard any number of Item cards you find there. Your opponent shuffles the other cards back into their deck.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Tyranitar
flavorText: If it rampages, it knocks down mountains and buries rivers. Maps must be redrawn afterward.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon-GX or a Pokémon-EX, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Poochyena
flavorText: It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Darkness Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Mightyena
flavorText: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.
Attack2Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Absol
flavorText: Although it's said to bring disaster, in actuality, this Pokémon possesses a calm disposition and warns people of any crises that loom.
Ability1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, its Retreat Cost is Colorless more.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

name: Spiritomb
flavorText: It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 4 Pokémon and discard them. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Zorua
flavorText: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Zoroark
flavorText: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile. You can't do more than 200 damage in this way.

name: Vullaby
flavorText: It can't fly yet and must wait until its wings have developed more. Since it's still at a playful age, it hops around friskily.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Mandibuzz
flavorText: It circles in the sky, keeping a keen eye out for Pokémon in a weakened state. Its choicest food is Cubone.
Attack1Text: Discard an Item card from your hand. If you do, this attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon does 30 damage to itself.

name: Pangoro
flavorText: From the slight twitches of its bamboo leaf, it deduces its opponent's movements. It's eager to tussle but kindhearted toward its companions.
Attack1Text: Your opponent discards 2 cards from their hand.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Yveltal
flavorText: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.
Attack1Text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Hoopa-GX
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon can't use Dark Strike during your next turn.

name: Incineroar-GX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put 3 damage counters on this Pokémon. If you do, search your deck for up to 3 Darkness Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Skarmory
flavorText: Its metal body is sturdy, but it does rust rather easily. So on rainy days, this Pokémon prefers to stay put in its nest.
Attack1Text: If you have used your GX attack, this attack does 70 more damage.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Jirachi
flavorText: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, you may look at the top 5 cards of your deck, reveal a Trainer card you find there, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle the other cards back into your deck, and this Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Bronzor
flavorText: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.
Ability1Text: If you go second, this Pokémon can evolve during your first turn.

name: Bronzong
flavorText: Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong for rain was the way to make crops grow.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Fire Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Ferroseed
flavorText: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Ferrothorn
flavorText: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage times the amount of Metal Energy attached to this Pokémon to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. You can't do more than 100 damage to a Benched Pokémon in this way. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Pawniard
flavorText: Ignoring their injuries, groups attack by sinking the blades that cover their bodies into their prey.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Bisharp
flavorText: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon has no damage counters on it, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Cobalion-GX
Ability1Text: Each of your Pokémon that has any Metal Energy attached to it can't be affected by any Special Conditions. Remove any Special Conditions affecting those Pokémon.
Attack1Text: If there is any Stadium card in play, this attack does 60 more damage.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, their Pokémon can't attack. (This includes Pokémon that come into play on that turn.) (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Honedge
flavorText: If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person's arm and drains that person's life energy completely.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Doublade
flavorText: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each Pokémon Tool card attached to all Pokémon.

name: Aegislash
flavorText: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon takes 40 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Klefki
flavorText: It never lets go of a key that it likes, so people give it the keys to vaults and safes as a way to prevent crime.
Ability1Text: Each of your Metal Pokémon's Resistance is now -40.

name: Alolan Ninetales
flavorText: It creates drops of ice in its coat and showers them over its enemies. Anyone who angers it will be frozen stiff in an instant.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon by your opponent's Pokémon-GX or Pokémon-EX.

name: Mimikyu
flavorText: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Pokémon used an attack that isn't a GX attack during their last turn, use it as this attack.

name: Latias & Latios-GX
Attack1Text: Discard 3 Energy from this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Attach 5 basic Energy cards from your discard pile to your Pokémon in any way you like. If this Pokémon has at least 1 extra Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to it during your opponent's next turn. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Alolan Exeggutor
flavorText: As it grew taller and taller, it outgrew its reliance on psychic powers, while within it awakened the power of the sleeping dragon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each type of basic Energy card in your discard pile. You can't add more than 100 damage in this way.

name: Alolan Exeggutor
flavorText: Exeggutor is the pride of the Alolan people. Its image is carved into historical buildings and murals.
Attack1Text: You may discard any number of cards from your hand. Then, draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
Attack2Text: Discard any number of Exeggcute from your hand. This attack does 60 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Dratini
flavorText: It's still weak, so it lurks on the floor of bodies of water, eating whatever food sinks down and living a quiet life.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Dratini
flavorText: It's still weak, so it lurks on the floor of bodies of water, eating whatever food sinks down and living a quiet life.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's attacks, except damage, done to this Pokémon.

name: Dragonair
flavorText: Lakes where Dragonair live are filled with offerings from people, because they believe this Pokémon is able to control the weather.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon. If both of them are tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Dragonite
flavorText: It flies over raging seas as if they were nothing. Observing this, a ship's captain dubbed this Pokémon "the sea incarnate."
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Eevee & Snorlax-GX
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
Attack1Text: Attach an Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is an Evolution Pokémon, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Pidgey
flavorText: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Pidgey
flavorText: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Pidgeotto
flavorText: The claws on its feet are well developed. It can carry prey such as an Exeggcute to its nest over 60 miles away.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may look at the top 2 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Put the other card on the bottom of your deck.

name: Pidgeot
flavorText: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent puts their Active Pokémon and all cards attached to it into their hand.

name: Meowth
flavorText: When visiting a junkyard, you may catch sight of it having an intense fight with Murkrow over shiny objects.

name: Persian
flavorText: Although the jewel on its forehead appears to be a different color than those of Alolan Persian, it's mostly made of the same material.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has 4 or more cards in their hand, they reveal their hand. Discard cards you find there until your opponent has exactly 4 cards in their hand.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Farfetch'd
flavorText: The plant stalk it holds is its weapon. The stalk is used like a sword to cut all sorts of things.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tool cards from your opponent's Active Pokémon. If you discarded a Pokémon Tool card in this way, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Kangaskhan
flavorText: Kangaskhan protects its child by keeping it in its pouch. It has zero forgiveness for those who harm its child and will beat them down.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Evolution Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Tauros
flavorText: They live in groups. The one with the longest, thickest, and most-scarred horns is the boss of the herd.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on all of your Tauros and Tauros-GX.

name: Aerodactyl
flavorText: Restored from DNA found in amber, this Pokémon exhibited ferocity that was greater than expected. Some casualties resulted.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: If you don't have any Pokémon-GX or Pokémon-EX on your Bench, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Lugia
flavorText: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Zangoose
flavorText: Its fur would all stand on end if it smelled a Seviper nearby. Its sharp claws tear up its foes.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 6 cards of your deck, reveal any number of Pokémon you find there, and put them into your hand. Discard the other cards.

name: Celebi & Venusaur-GX
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned, Confused, and Poisoned.
